sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant LS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Inference<br/>configurable/TCP
    participant vLLMEmb as vLLM Embedding<br/>configurable/TCP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Milvus as Milvus / pgvector / Qdrant<br/>configurable/TCP
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI FMS<br/>configurable/TCP HTTPS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>configurable/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Chat Completion via vLLM

    Client->>LS: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP, No Auth
    LS->>vLLM: Forward inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Bearer Token
    vLLM-->>LS: Completion response
    LS->>PG: Log inference (async write queue)<br/>PostgreSQL, Username/Password
    LS-->>Client: JSON Response (OpenAI-compatible)

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

    Client->>LS: POST /v1/agents/*<br/>HTTP, No Auth
    LS->>Milvus: Vector similarity search<br/>HTTP/gRPC/PostgreSQL, Token/Password
    Milvus-->>LS: Relevant document chunks
    LS->>vLLMEmb: Generate embeddings (if needed)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Bearer Token
    vLLMEmb-->>LS: Embedding vectors
    LS->>vLLM: Inference with retrieved context<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Bearer Token
    vLLM-->>LS: Augmented completion
    LS-->>Client: Agent response with RAG context

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Model Evaluation via Kubeflow Pipelines

    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/*<br/>HTTP, No Auth
    LS->>KFP: Submit evaluation pipeline<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Bearer Token (KUBEFLOW_PIPELINES_TOKEN)
    KFP->>S3: Store evaluation results<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS credentials
    KFP-->>LS: Pipeline run status + results
    LS-->>Client: Evaluation results

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 4: Safety Guardrail Check

    Client->>LS: POST /v1/safety/*<br/>HTTP, No Auth
    LS->>TrustyAI: Safety shield evaluation<br/>HTTPS, TLS (custom cert FMS_SSL_CERT_PATH)
    TrustyAI-->>LS: Safety verdict (pass/fail/warn)
    LS-->>Client: Safety evaluation result
